import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size().reset_index(name='size')
    sns.histplot(data=group_sizes, x='size', kde=True, color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Sizes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(['Group Sizes'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    average_group_size = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().mean()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='group', y='person', data=data, estimator=len, ci=None)
    ax.axhline(average_group_size, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Group Size: {average_group_size:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Group Size')
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group', hue='person', multiple='stack', legend=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people per group?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Person', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts().reset_index()
    group_counts.columns = ['group', 'count']
    chart = sns.barplot(x='group', y='count', data=group_counts, palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    chart.legend(title='Group Size', loc='upper right', labels=group_counts['group'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
